This sixth studio album from the unassuming studio genius follows 2005&#039;s &#039;Hotel&#039; 
and has been described by the man himself as a return to a more electronic and
dancefloor oriented feel. Produced and recorded at his home studio in Manhattan,
 the record includes the single &#039;Alice&#039; and features a variety of guest vocalists
 including the UK&#039;s MC Aynzli, Sylvia Gordon of Brooklyn indie-dance outfit Kudu, 
the Yoruba-speaking Nigerian 419 Crew, and Grandmaster Caz, one of the writers of
 the seminal hip-hop anthem &#039;Rapper&#039;s Delight&#039;.
